IAM Policy ‚Äì Permissions (Access to Kinesis)

{
  "Sid": "ReadStream",
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": [
    "kinesis:DescribeStreamSummary",
    "kinesis:GetShardIterator",
    "kinesis:GetRecords",
    "kinesis:ListShards",
    "kinesis:DescribeStream"
  ],
  "Resource": "arn:aws:kinesis:*:<account>:stream/*"
},
{
  "Sid": "ListStream",
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": "kinesis:ListStreams",
  "Resource": "*"
}

üßæ Purpose:

This permissions policy allows an IAM role to read data from Amazon Kinesis Data Streams. Specifically:

DescribeStream / ListShards / GetShardIterator / GetRecords ‚Äì Needed to access and read records from a Kinesis stream.

ListStreams ‚Äì Allows listing all available Kinesis streams.

ü§ù 2. Trust Policy ‚Äì Assume Role

{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Principal": {
    "Service": [
      "events.amazonaws.com",
      "redshift.amazonaws.com"
    ]
  },
  "Action": "sts:AssumeRole",
  "Condition": {
    "StringEquals": {
      "AWS:SourceAccount": "1234567890"
    },
    "ArnEquals": {
      "AWS:SourceArn": "arn:aws:dms:us-east-1:1234567890:rep:6LO4G7A4SNG4PC732QEDP772OY"
    }
  }
}

üîê Purpose:

This trust policy allows AWS services to assume the IAM role so they can access Kinesis. Specifically:

Principal: events.amazonaws.com ‚Üí Lets Amazon EventBridge assume the role.

Principal: redshift.amazonaws.com ‚Üí Lets Amazon Redshift assume the role (e.g., for streaming ingestion from Kinesis).

A specific AWS account (1234567890)
